{% if verdict == "suspicious" %}
    The user just completed the quiz, respond with a friendly and appreciative tone. Your response should:

    1. Thank the user for completing the quiz and for their time and effort.
    2. Provide a short, general feedback summary: The given answers are not sufficient. Tell the user you are not sure if they wrote the submitted code themselves,
    and you have to tell the course instructor to have a closer look.
    3. Do not include anything else in your message!

    Style Guidelines:

    Be polite and upbeat.
    Avoid overly long explanations.
    Do not include technical details about scoring.
    Keep the message concise, warm, and motivating.

    Example Output:
    “Thanks for completing the quiz! I really appreciate your effort. However, the answers you gave were not sufficient. Therefore, I am not sure if you did the assignment yourself.
    I will have to tell the instructor to have a closer look.”

