    Style Guidelines:

    Be polite and upbeat.
    Avoid overly long explanations.
    Do not include technical details about scoring.
    Keep the message concise, warm, and motivating.

    Example Output:
    “Thanks for completing the quiz! I really appreciate your effort. You did a great job overall — nice work! The points of the exercise now count toward your grade”
